One year ago, a terrorist attack at Abbey Gate outside the Kabul Airport resulted in the deaths of 13 American service members and over 100 innocent Afghan civilians. The article highlights the names of the fallen soldiers and expresses condolences to their families. It recognizes their bravery and selflessness in serving their country during a noble mission. The US government has intensified its efforts to combat terrorism following the attack, eliminating key leaders of ISIS and al-Qaeda. The administration pledges to continue hunting down terrorists wherever they may be. The article also acknowledges the sacrifices made by the families and survivors of those who lost their lives in the Afghanistan war, emphasizing the high cost and lasting impact of war. Gratitude is expressed to the Armed Forces, veterans, diplomats, and other professionals who served in Afghanistan and contributed to strengthening national security.